node.text: Designed by Roland Meyer-Brühl. This architecturally distinct corner solution consisting of longchair and swivel sofa provides intelligent transformation options and excellent comfort. Beneath the sofa’s armrest a table can be found. The recamier’s armrest can be pulled forwards and thus turns into a backrest when sitting down. All covers removable. Based on a chrome frame and fitted with aluminium castors. Tap for more www.modumshop.com

node.title: Four-Two Multifunctional Sofa for Small Interiors by @modumshop.de

node.text:
Custom rugs by @locarpet_craft come in various designs that have their own value for their audience. A rug that not only can be room decorations but also can be sentimental works.

Rug Artisan that is based in Indonesia, Locarpet has its own quality with a good selection of materials, accurate details. Also, Locarpet is always doing a lot of crazy developments with rugs.

That’s why their rugs always have a strong sentimental value. Because the quality that is done is also of the best. Even with complex designs, Locarpet is always detailed in working on the game. 
Visit @locarpet_craft to see more amazing rugs!

node.text: JUST LAUNCHED! This nature-inspired rug by British designer @sonyawinnerrugs 🌄 The Colour Canyon Rug is inspired by the breathtaking natural beauty of Arizona's Grand Canyon. A fluid design, celebrating the union of vibrant colours and calming organic shapes. Entirely handmade in traditional weaving communities by artisan weavers.

node.text:
@Umithan_Ucok created a pack you'd want to keep after purchasing your new favourite pair of shoes. 
“RamPack" shoe packaging was developed to prevent throwing away shoeboxes immediately after purchasing. It functions as a shoe carrier and also a storage box, thus extending the life of the shoe packaging. 

It has paper rope handles for carrying so it can be transported without the need for an additional carrier bag. The handles are connected to the lid of the box and a recess in the lid prevents them from getting in the way during stacking. The green cover is removed in order to try on the shoes.

After the RamPack is purchased, the box turns into a shoe ramp by tearing away the green coloured parts of the box. This allows the shoes to be stored more efficiently at home.

node.text:
Hope Ceramics are not just about beautiful vases. This is the story of Ayca and Nadège, who found their kindred spirit in a fellow female creative. Ayca is the name behind @Mara.Paris jewelry brand. While she was working on HOPE Collection, she met Nadège, a highly talented ceramic artist. Together, they decided to transform the Hope shape into something bigger, into an art form that could live eternally on the body and beyond.

Nadège crafts her vases by hand in her Parisian atelier. Like anything made with love by an artisan, her vases take time to produce, and nothing is left to chance. That’s why they decided to produce limited amount of vases for each model.

node.text:
This railing on a gazebo in Naples has braille describing the view for blind people! 

The 92-foot-long piece of steel is etched with braille, describing the stunning view for the blind people. 
The unique railing was installed in 2015 by artist Paolo Puddu and is titled “Follow the Shape”, which has been a permanent fixture of the castle ever since. 

Blind visitors are encouraged to run their hands along the railing to read verses from The Land and The Man: a poetry series from Italian author Giuseppe de Lorenzo. 
The inscription is carved in both Italian and English, as tourists are prompted to imagine the stunning view in front of them.
